      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "NSW Oaks winner GLADIATRIX (6) raced parked but stuck on to place behind a handy one last time after leading from a similar draw and scoring by 5m two back. Drops to a distance where she has won five of seven attempts, all of them here. She looks the standout in a highly winnable assignment. CEE CEE IN PARIS (5) was one spot behind GLADIATRIX last time and also chased her as runner-up prior. It won't be easy to turn the tables on that rival but she is going well enough to be in the finish. BROTHER MOUNTAIN (4) brings good form from Victoria where he won two back at Melton before a second at Bendigo last week. Has recorded a win and a placing in two tries at the mile so can be competitive along with PURPLE MOON (3) who is starting to deliver now, beating GLADIATRIX home when runner-up at big odds two back before breaking her maiden here last week.",
